content.description: This route starts on the same crimps as [Natural Selection]]107830609, but instead of doing a big dyno out right, you follow the line straight up the roof, doing a gaston move with the right hand to a good pocket, then topping out trending left to jugs on the roof (per Christian Klaiber).
content.location:

content.description:
I know for sure I am not the first person to do this, so let me know if you've got info on the problem.

Start on two crimps on the left side of the overhung face. Make an all points off dyno to the good dish. From there, make another big move to the lip right below the top of the boulder. Top out straight up (the same way you top out

The Millennium Falcon

).

The first move isn't necessarily hard, it's just not natural, but it's a great move.
content.location: This is on the left side of the west overhanging face of the Millennium Falcon Boulder.

content.description: Climb the obvious line along the juggy overhang to the carved out dish.  Make an awkward mantle to the top.
content.location: Upon entering Dynamite Shacks parking area, follow the first trail leading right (back toward GJ) all the way to its end, and the problem is obvious.
